* ============================================================
* FINAL BLOWOUT TEST (PARKED / DISABLED)
*
* Purpose:
*   Reserved slot for the eventual large-size X64 memo stress test.
*
* Status:
*   DO NOT ENABLE until:
*     - CREATE X64 is stable
*     - repeated memo self-append is stable
*     - close/reopen persistence is stable
*     - clear/reinsert is stable
*     - no corruption/truncation is observed in normal growth tests
*
* Intended future behavior:
*   Grow NOTES far beyond the baseline and stage-2 tests, using a
*   dedicated large-chunk method once available.
*
* Preferred future implementation:
*   1) file-to-memo ingestion, or
*   2) purpose-built MEMOFILL / MEMOSTRESS command, or
*   3) loop/variable support mature enough for safe scripted growth
*
* Suggested future checkpoints:
*   - 1 MB
*   - 10 MB
*   - 100 MB
*   - 1 GB
*   - 2 GB
*   - 4 GB+
*
* Suggested future proof points:
*   - write succeeds
*   - reopen succeeds
*   - DISPLAY still works
*   - TUPLE still works sensibly
*   - memo clear still works
*   - reinsert after clear still works
*   - no DBF/DTX corruption
*
